# Hawkeye Sterling — Code Owners
#
# Ownership routing for review governance. GitHub automatically requests a
# review from the matching owner(s) when a pull request touches a path below.
# The LAST matching pattern wins, so ordering is significant.
#
# Security-, audit-, and compliance-critical paths are owned by the repository
# maintainer and cannot be merged without that review (enforced by branch
# protection: "Require review from Code Owners"). See GOVERNANCE.md for the
# decision-rights model and CONTRIBUTING.md for the local gate.

